      <abstract>
        <p>New York City Mayor Michael R Bloomberg receives Abraham Lincoln Award from Illinois Council Against Handgun Violence for Bloomberg effort against illegal guns; reminds crowd he was last in Illinois when he tried to woo 2008 Democratic Convention to New York, and says Lincoln is his role model; photo (M)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Mayor Michael R. Bloomberg offered a coy reference to the 2008 presidential election on Wednesday night in Chicago, in dinner remarks to the Illinois Council Against Handgun Violence, which gave the mayor its Abraham Lincoln Award for his efforts to combat illegal guns.</p>
